<TITLE> Cousels allege torture on Mahmudur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Lawyers for Mahmudur Rahman, the detained acting editor of the recently closed down Bengali daily Amar Desh, alleged torture on their client in court custody on Wednesday. The two lawyers, Sanaullah Miah and Masud Ahmed Talukder, visited him at court custody around 4pm after getting approval from Dhaka's Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. In a following press briefing at BNP chairperson's Gulshan office, Sanaullah Miah, also the Dhaka Lawyers Association chief, said, "Our client informed us that he was not given water for over 15 hours." "We entered his cell to see him lying on the floor with a book under his head. The cell has no chairs," he added. The lawyers also alleged that initially the police did not allow them to visit Mahmudur despite the court approval. They also claimed that Mahmudur was not being provided food either. BNP's senior joint secretary general Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir was present at the press briefing among others
